The paper discusses the use of machine learning models with algorithms built with respect for user privacy, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of blockchain technology to ensure on-device privacy, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of decentralized learning, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of data sharing and network architecture, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
